etymologies: 1930s; earliest use found in Popular Science Monthly. From rocket + fuel

definitions: Fuel for a rocket engine; specifically one that reacts with an oxidizer.

notes.text: Fuel and oxidizer collectively are propellants.

definitions: In extended use: something which has a stimulating or energizing effect; specifically a strong alcoholic drink.
The veterinary analgesic and anaesthetic phencyclidine, used as a recreational drug.
